modules.description: Encodes `Received.t` values into structured output formats. It provides functions to serialize received fields with precise formatting and indentation. Useful for generating human-readable representations of email headers or network protocol data.

Decodes structured timestamps from network message headers using Angstrom parsers. It operates on `Received.t` values, which represent timestamp data, and provides a parser for converting raw byte strings into timestamp records. This is used in network protocol implementations to extract and validate timestamp fields from received packets.
